cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "BioThreat-Eval: LLM Biosecurity Capability Evaluation Pipeline"
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: JangKeun
    affiliation: "Weill Cornell Medicine"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-04-04"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/jang1563/biothreat-eval"
abstract: >
  A systematic pipeline for evaluating how frontier language models handle
  dual-use biological knowledge queries, translating behavioral profiles into
  quantitative risk assessments and policy recommendations using a 4-stage
  Monte Carlo attack chain model calibrated against NSABB dual-use categories.
keywords:
  - biosecurity
  - large language models
  - dual-use research of concern
  - ai safety
  - risk assessment
  - NSABB
